President Donald J. Trump has announced his intention to nominate Sethuraman Panchanathan for the position of Director of the National Science Foundation. Panchanathan is currently the Executive Vice President and Chief Research and Innovation Officer at Arizona State University (ASU). He has also served as the Founding Director of the Center for Cognitive Ubiquitous Computing at ASU. Panchanathan has been appointed to the National Science Board (NSB) and has held various positions within the field of innovation and entrepreneurship. He is a Fellow of several prestigious organizations and has a strong educational background in physics, engineering, and computer science.